.TH SKIPPY-XD 1 "October 2025" "skippy-xd v0.10.4 (2025.10.05) - 'Standpipe' Edition MUSQ" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
skippy-xd - lightweight X11 window selector with
switch/expose/paging.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B skippy-xd
.RI [ COMMAND  ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B skippy-xd
is a lightweight, window-manager-agnostic window
selector for the X server. It provides three window 
management modes: switch (similar to Alt-Tab with
live preview), expose (inspired by macOS), and paging
(overview of all virtual desktops). These can be
activated via toggle or pivot activation modes.
.PP
The application works as a daemon that can be
controlled via command-line interface. When run without
arguments, it activates expose mode once without
starting the daemon.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Daemon Management
.TP
.B --start-daemon
Start skippy-xd in daemon mode. The daemon runs in
the background and waits for commands from the
command line interface.
.TP
.B --stop-daemon
Terminate the running skippy-xd daemon.
.SS Activation Metaphors
.TP
.B --switch [--prev|--next]
Activate switch mode via the daemon. This mode
is similar to Alt-Tab and allows quick window switching
with live preview. Use
.B --prev
to focus on the previous window or
.B --next
to focus on the next window.
.TP
.B --expose
Activate expose mode via the daemon. This shows a
live preview of all open windows on the current
desktop, inspired by macOS Exposé.
.TP
.B --paging
Activate paging mode via the daemon. This displays
an overview of all virtual desktops, allowing easy
navigation and switching between desktops.
.TP
.B --multi-select
Enable multi-select mode to select multiple windows
and return all their Window IDs.
.SS Activation Modes (Toggle and Pivot)
.TP
.B --toggle
Activate via toggle mode. Command toggles skippy-xd
activation on/off.
.TP
.B --pivot
.I KEY
Activate via pivot mode with the specified pivot key.
For example in Alt-Tab, Alt is the pivot key,
required to be held for activation. When the pivot
key is released, the currently highlighted window is
selected.
.SS Window Filtering
.TP
.B --wm-class
.I CLASS
Display only windows belonging to the specified WM
class.
.TP
.B --wm-title
.I TITLE
Display only windows matching the specified title.
.TP
.B --wm-status
.I STATUS
Display only windows with the specified status.
Valid status values are:
.RS
.IP "sticky" 4
Sticky windows (visible on all desktops)
.IP "shaded" 4
Shaded windows
.IP "minimized" 4
Minimized windows
.IP "float" 4
Floating windows
.IP "maximized_vert" 4
Vertically maximized windows
.IP "maximized_horz" 4
Horizontally maximized windows
.IP "maximized" 4
Fully maximized windows
.RE
.TP
.B --desktop
.I DESKTOP
Display only windows on the specified virtual
desktop. Use
.B -1
to show windows from all desktops.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B --prev
Focus on the previous window in the current
selection.
.TP
.B --next
Focus on the next window in the current selection.
.SS Configuration
.TP
.B --config
.I PATH
Load or reload the configuration file from the
specified path. The daemon will read this
configuration file at startup. See
https://github.com/felixfung/skippy-xd/wiki/Config#config-file-reloading
for more information on config file reloading.
.TP
.B --config-reload
Reload the configuration file without changing the
path. Useful for applying config changes without
restarting the daemon.
.SS Utilities
.TP
.B --help
Display the help message showing all available
commands.
.TP
.B --debug-log
Enable debugging logs for troubleshooting.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/skippy-xd/skippy-xd.rc
Default user configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/xdg/skippy-xd/skippy-xd.sample.rc
Sample configuration file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Starting the Daemon
.IP
.B skippy-xd --start-daemon
.PP
Starts the skippy-xd daemon in the background.
.IP
.B skippy-xd --start-daemon --config ~/.config/skippy-xd/skippy-xd.rc
.PP
Starts the skippy-xd daemon in the background
using the specified configuration file.
.SS Window Switching
.IP
.B skippy-xd --switch --next
.PP
Focus on the next window in switch mode.
.IP
.B skippy-xd --switch --prev
.PP
Focus on the previous window in switch mode.
.SS Viewing All Windows
.IP
.B skippy-xd --expose
.PP
Show live preview of all windows on the current
desktop.
.SS Desktop Overview
.IP
.B skippy-xd --paging
.PP
Display overview of all virtual desktops.
.SS Filtered Window Selection
.IP
.B skippy-xd --expose --wm-class firefox
.PP
Show only Firefox windows in expose mode.
.IP
.B skippy-xd --expose --desktop 1
.PP
Show windows only from desktop 1.
.SS Additional Examples
.IP
.B skippy-xd --expose --pivot Super_L --next
.PP
Activate expose metaphor via pivot mode with Super_L
as the pivot key, highlighting the next window.
.IP
.B skippy-xd --expose --desktop -1 --wm-class firefox --wm-status float,maximized_vert --config ~/.config/skippy-xd/other.rc
.PP
Show Firefox windows from all desktops that are
floating or vertically maximized. Using a custom config file.
.SS One-shot Expose
.IP
.B skippy-xd
.PP
Activate expose mode once without starting the
daemon.
